During a virtual court hearing, a senior lawyer was caught drinking beer, talking on the phone, and using a holiday-themed wallpaper as his background. The unprofessional conduct sparked widespread criticism and led the Gujarat High Court to take strict action against him. The incident has raised serious concerns about courtroom decorum and respect for judicial proceedings in the era of virtual hearings. Authorities are reviewing the case to ensure such behaviour is not repeated.

[Virtual court misconduct, Gujarat High Court]

#NewsWithET

Delhi High Court has granted bail to Neelam Azad and Mahesh Kumawat, accused in the December 2023 Parliament breach, on a Rs 50,000 bond each. The court barred them from media interviews, social media posts, and travelling outside Delhi-NCR without permission. They must report to police thrice a week at 10 am.

[Delhi High Court, Parliament]
